           <h1 class="title" id="page-title">Help <em>World Literature Today</em> Magazine, Your Passport to Great Reading, Raise $10,000 in 24 Hours!</h1>
      
          
    
          <div class="date-display-single">April 7, 2026</div>
    
          <div class="field-name-field-author field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix">
        <div class="field-label"><em>by</em>&nbsp;
                              <a href="/author/editors-wlt">The Editors of WLT</a>
                                                                                              </div>
      </div>
    
    
    
    <div class="content pigeon-first-p">
	    <div class="pigeon-context-promotion" style="display:none;">
	      <p>This page is available to subscribers. <a href="https://my.worldlit.org" class="pigeon-open">Click here to sign in or get access</a>.</p>
      </div>
      
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><!-- THEME DEBUG --><!-- THEME HOOK: 'insert_image' --><!-- BEGIN OUTPUT from 'sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/modules/contrib/insert/templates/insert-image.html.twig' --><img src="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/26_960x640_GD_anchor.jpg" data-entity-uuid="insert-image-aec7e93e-2873-4cea-8a5e-e2119f37e561" data-entity-type="file" alt="Text reads: Help WLT reach raise $10k in 24 hours. #OUGivingDay. April 14, 2026" width="960" height="640" loading="lazy"><!-- END OUTPUT from 'sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/modules/contrib/insert/templates/insert-image.html.twig' --><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Over the next eight days—between now and&nbsp;<a href="https://givesooner.org/">Giving Day</a> (April 14)—your gift will help <em>World Literature Today </em>(<span class="small-caps">wlt</span>) further its mission: to serve students and readers everywhere with outstanding, timely coverage of world literature and culture. For 100 years and counting, <em>WLT</em> has been a window to the world, providing what Maya Angelou once called “absolutely the most welcome reading I’ve found in years.”</p><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Here’s how you can help us reach our $10,000 goal:</p><ul style="list-style-type:disc;"><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">For a <strong>$25 </strong>gift, you will receive a one-year subscription to the digital edition of <em>World Literature Today</em> magazine.</p></li><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">With your <strong>$50 </strong>donation, in addition to a one-year digital subscription, we’ll send you a set of limited-edition postcards that feature quotable quotes from recent <em>WLT</em> contributors: 2024 Nobel Prize winner Han Kang, 2025 Puterbaugh Fellow Guadalupe Nettel, 2024 Neustadt Prize laureate Ananda Devi, 2023 NSK Prize winner Gene Yang, and award-winning Turkish writer Elif Shafak.</p></li><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">For a <strong>$100</strong> gift, <em>WLT</em> will donate a copy of <em>A Compass on the Navigable Sea</em>, the brand-new <em>WLT</em>&nbsp;<a href="https://restlessbooks.org/bookstore/compass-on-the-navigable-sea">centennial anthology</a>, to a student, school library, or public library of your choice (U.S. addresses only).</p></li><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">With your <strong>$250 </strong>donation, you can give or receive a one-year subscription to the print edition of the magazine (U.S. addresses only), a set of postcards, and a copy of <em>A Compass on the Navigable Sea</em>.</p></li></ul><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">We are also participating in two&nbsp;<a href="https://givesooner.org/pages/ou-challenges">challenges</a>:</p><ul style="list-style-type:disc;"><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">From 1:00-2:00am <span class="small-caps">cdt</span> , the <strong>Farthest Gift from Norman</strong> hourly challenge (with a special appeal to our readers in Africa, Europe, the Middle East, and Asia)</p></li><li><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Throughout the day, the <strong>OU Faculty/Staff: Most Gifts</strong> mega challenge</p></li></ul><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Visit&nbsp;<a href="https://givesooner.org/">givesooner.org</a> to help us raise $10,000 in 24 hours! Click on the “Make a Gift” button and enter “<strong>World Literature Today</strong>” in the search funds field. Gifts in any amount are welcome.</p><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">To learn more about the $4 million&nbsp;<a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/donate">March to 100</a> campaign—which will help <em>WLT</em> endow its future for the next hundred years—visit the&nbsp;<a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/donate">donate</a> page on our website.</p><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Questions? Please call 405-325-0317 or email&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#fd8f9e999c8b948ebd9288d3989988"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="5022333431263923103f257e353425">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>.</p><p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">#OUGivingDay<br>April 14, 2026</p></div>
